data.text:
List of famous film actors and actresses from Australia, listed by their popularity with photos when available. Australia has given birth to some great movie actors and actresses over the years, many of who have gone on to star in comedies, dramas, horror movies and more. These are some of the best Australian screen actors in the history of the world, so if you're a native of Australia and an aspiring actor/actress then these are people you should look up to.

List features film actors like Noel Tovey and Warren Coleman.

This list answers the questions, "Who are the best Australian actors?" and "Which movies stars are from Australia?"

You can click on the names of these legendary movie stars of Australia in order to get more information about each one. If you're a film buff use this list of talented Australian film actors to find some new movies you haven't already seen.

Ranked by

Batman Forever, Moulin Rouge!, Eyes Wide Shut

Birthplace : Honolulu, Hawaii, USA

Nationality : United States of America, Australia

Height : 5'10"

Parents : Janelle Ann Kidman, Antony Kidman

Children : Connor Cruise, Faith Margaret Kidman Urban, Sunday Rose Kidman Urban, Isabella Jane Cruise

Nicole Kidman, an Academy Award-winning actress, has captivated audiences with her stunning performances across various genres. With films like Moulin Rouge!, The Others, and Big Little Lies under her belt, Kidman's versatility is undeniable. Known for her ethereal beauty and grace, Nicole Kidman remains an influential figure in the world of cinema.

The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King, The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring, The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers

Birthplace : Melbourne, Victoria, Australia

Nationality : Australia

Height : 5'8"

Parents : Robert Blanchett, June Blanchett

Children : Ignatius Martin Upton, Roman Robert Upton, Dashiell John Upton

Cate Blanchett's illustrious career is marked by remarkable portrayals of diverse, complex characters. As an accomplished stage and screen actor, Blanchett has won numerous awards for her roles, including two Oscars. With standout performances in Elizabeth, Blue Jasmine, and Carol, Cate Blanchett proves time and time again that she is a powerhouse talent.

X-Men, X-Men: First Class, X-Men: The Last Stand

Birthplace : Sydney, New South Wales, Australia

Nationality : Australia

Height : 6'2"

Parents : Grace McNeil, Christopher John Jackman

Children : Ava Eliot Jackman, Oscar Maximilian Jackman

Hugh Jackman cannot be contained by just one genre; he has touched every corner of the acting world, from his iconic portrayal of Wolverine in the X-Men franchise to singing and dancing in The Greatest Showman. Jackman, a versatile and charismatic performer, consistently showcases his passion for acting. No matter the role, fans eagerly anticipate what Hugh Jackman will do next.

The Dark Knight, Brokeback Mountain, The Patriot

Birthplace : Perth, Australia

Nationality : Australia

Height : 6'0"

Parents : Sally Ledger Bell, Kim Ledger

Children : Matilda Ledger

Heath Ledger left an indelible mark on the world of film with his intense, methodical performances. Best remembered for his haunting portrayal of the Joker in The Dark Knight, Ledger's untimely death only further immortalized his talent. Nevertheless, movies like Brokeback Mountain, Candy, and A Knight's Tale are just a few examples of Heath Ledger's unforgettable body of work.

The Dark Knight Rises, Knowing, The Place Beyond the Pines

Birthplace : Melbourne, Victoria, Australia

Nationality : Australia

Parents : Carole Ann Ferguson Mendelsohn, Frederick Arthur Oscar Mendelsohn

Ben Mendelsohn's career has spanned decades, filled with diverse roles that showcase his exceptional acting range. He first gained international recognition as Danny Rayburn on Netflix's Bloodline and has since made memorable appearances in acclaimed films such as Rogue One: A Star Wars Story and Ready Player One. Mendelsohn's ability to delve deep into the psyche of his characters makes him a captivating presence on-screen.

The Adventures of Robin Hood, Cinema Paradiso, Captain Blood

Birthplace : Hobart, Australia

Nationality : United Kingdom, Australia, United States of America

Height : 6'2"

Parents : Theodore Thomson Flynn, Lily Mary Young Flynn

Children : Sean Flynn, Deirdre Flynn, Rory Flynn, Arnella Roma Flynn

Errol Flynn's legendary status as the quintessential swashbuckler and romantic lead endures to this day. In the 1930s and '40s, Flynn starred in classics such as The Adventures of Robin Hood and Captain Blood, which solidified his place in Hollywood history. With his suave charm and devilish grin, Errol Flynn remains a symbol of glamour from cinema's Golden Age.
